NNAAMMEE
       ppuummmmeell - http load testing tool

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ppuummmmeell sstteepp [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s] [_u_r_l_-_f_i_l_e]

       ppuummmmeell lliimmiitt [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s] [_u_r_l_-_f_i_l_e]

       ppuummmmeell bbeenncchhmmaarrkk [_o_p_t_i_o_n_s] [_u_r_l_-_f_i_l_e]

       ppuummmmeell aannaallyyzzee

       ppuummmmeell hheellpp [[<<ccoommmmaanndd>>]]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       Pummel  is an HTTP load generation and measurement tool. It is designed
       to help find the concurrency limits of an HTTP  server  relative  to  a
       specified  latency  latency  at  a  given percentile. For instance, the
       incantation:



           pummel limit --percentile 99.9 --target 50 ./urls.txt



       would search for the highest concurrency  level  which  will  keep  the
       99.9th percentile response times below 50 milliseconds.

       Alternately,  pummel may be used for exploratory testing. The step com-
       mand is particularly useful for his, such as:



           pummel step --percentile 99.9 --step 'c * 2' ./urls.txt



       will double the concurrency for  each  run,  printing  the  concurrency
       level,  latency at the specified percentile, mean latency, and requests
       per second at that concurrency level.

FFIILLEESS
       Pummel takes as input a sequence of URLs, one per line, either on stan-
       dard  input  or specified in a urls file as a command line argument. It
       will build a FIFO queue of requests which will be pulled off  and  exe-
       cuted concurrently by the program.

CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
   lliimmiitt
       The  lliimmiitt command takes a list of urls from either standard in or from
       a file specifed as an argument to the command.

       --ll, ----llaabbeellss
              Print column labels in the output

       --mm _m_a_x_-_r_e_q_u_e_s_t_s, ----mmaaxx _m_a_x_-_r_e_q_u_e_s_t_s
              Maximum number of requests to execute

       --pp _p_e_r_c_e_n_t_i_l_e, ----ppeerrcceennttiillee _p_e_r_c_e_n_t_i_l_e
              Percentile to try to target, default is 99th percentile

       --ss _s_t_a_r_t, ----ssttaarrtt _s_t_a_r_t
              Initial concurrency level, defaults to 100

       --tt _t_a_r_g_e_t, ----ttaarrggeett _t_a_r_g_e_t
              Target 99th percentile threshold, default is 100

   sstteepp
       The sstteepp command takes a list of urls from either standard in or from a
       file specifed as an argument to the command.

       --ll, ----llaabbeellss
              Show column labels

       --LL _l_i_m_i_t, ----lliimmiitt _l_i_m_i_t
              concurrency limit to stop at, default is 2147483647

       --mm _m_a_x_-_r_e_q_u_e_s_t_s, ----mmaaxx--rreeqquueessttss _m_a_x_-_r_e_q_u_e_s_t_s
              Maximum number of requests to execute

       --pp _p_e_r_c_e_n_t_i_l_e, ----ppeerrcceennttiillee _p_e_r_c_e_n_t_i_l_e
              Percentile to try to target, default is 99th percentile

       --ss _s_t_a_r_t, ----ssttaarrtt _s_t_a_r_t
              initial concurrency level, defaults to 100

       ----sstteepp _s_t_e_p_-_f_u_n_c_t_i_o_n
              Expression  used  to  calculate  the next concurrency level. The
              default is cc ++ 11 which increments the concurrency level by 1. It
              accepts  either  an MVEL Expression _h_t_t_p_:_/_/_m_v_e_l_._c_o_d_e_h_a_u_s_._o_r_g_/ or
              Clojure fucntion _h_t_t_p_:_/_/_c_l_o_j_u_r_e_._o_r_g_/ function. In the MVEL  case
              the  input level is contained in a variable named cc, in the clo-
              jure case it will be the lone argument to the function.

   bbeenncchhmmaarrkk
       The bbeenncchhmmaarrkk command takes a list of urls from either standard  in  or
       from a file specifed as an argument to the command.

       --cc _c_o_n_c_u_r_r_e_n_c_y, ----ccoonnccuurrrreennccyy _c_o_n_c_u_r_r_e_n_c_y
              Concurrency -- how many requests to keep in flight at once

       --mm _m_a_x_R_e_q_u_e_s_t_s, ----mmaaxx _m_a_x_R_e_q_u_e_s_t_s
              Maximum number of requests to execute

       --rr, ----rreeppoorrtt
              report basic stats on stderr when finished:

   aannaallyyzzee
       The  aannaallyyzzee  command takes a list of times, in millis, one per line on
       standard input. This is useful in combination with the  bbeenncchhmmaarrkk  com-
       mand.

